Also, turn in solutions to these exercises: 

Let m and n be positive integers.  Suppose that H is an m \times n matrix of zeros and ones.  Then we can can define a function e:\mathbb{Z}_2^m \rightarrow \mathbb{Z}_2^n by e(a)=a H where we take a \in \mathbb{Z}_2^m to be 1\times m matrix and we perform mod 2 arithmetic in computing the product a H.  Prove that e is a homomorphism.


The Hamming Distance, d, between two strings of bits with the same length is the number positions within the two strings where the strings differ.  For example, d(11101,10100)=2 because the two strings differ in positions 2 and 5.  What is the minimal Hamming distance between strings in the set \{000000,101010,010101,111111\}
